               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 4ra-13va)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 13va-28ra l.17)
 III) Anaphoras
                     (fols. 28ra, l.18–105ra l.19)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 28ra
                     l.18–35vb l.2)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ preceded by an
                     excerpt from the “Book of the Testament” (fols. 36ra–38rb l.19) (cp. MQ, IV,
                     Qǝddāse ʾǝgziʾ, §§1-17)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of
                     Behnesa (fols. 38rb l.20–47rb l.22)
 III-4) Anaphora of St John, Son of
                     Thunder (fols. 47va l.1–55vb l.7)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox
                     Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 55vb l.8–62va l.5)
 III-6) Anaphora of St John
                     Chrysostom (fols. 62va l.6–66vb l.2)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Dioscorus
                     (fols. 66vb l.3–69ra l.13)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Epiphanius (fols. 69ra
                     l.14-73va l.20)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Athanasius (fols. 73va l.21–82vb
                     l.2)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Gregory of Nyssa (“Hosanna-liturgy of St
                     Gregory”) (fols. 82vb l.3–87vb l.2)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug
                     (fols. 87vb l.3–92va l.8)
 III-12) (The first) Anaphora of St Cyril of
                     Alexandria (fols. 92va l.9–103ra l.12)
 III-13) The second Anaphora of St
                     Gregory (“Christmas-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols. 103ra l.13–105ra
                     l.19).</summary>
