                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the name of the reigning king; four
                           groups of lines (alternating with black lines) in the incipit page of
                           Text I; initial words or titles (parts of titles) of the texts; some of
                           the interlinear musical signs; directives fot the ministers and their
                           abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs.</seg>
